enter gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Benefits Of Using Deadlift Platform</h2></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1663068617795" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1663068617795"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Safe For Your Floor</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1663068617610" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1663068617610"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Perhaps the best reason for having a deadlift platform is that it will keep your floors safe. If you’re into powerlifting, then you’ll be used to deadlifting a lot of weight and all that weight will constantly hammer against your floor, and most likely hammer the same spot repeatedly, which can cause cracks and damage your floors.</p><p>If you’re into Olympic weightlifting, then the safest way to perform several of those exercises is to drop the weight from above, reset, and lift again, before dropping once more. This repeated process can also damage your floors even if you have a 3/4" rubber mat to absorb the force. Those mats can only absorb so much weight.&nbsp;</p><p>While a typical deadlift platform is made out of wood and is 8’x8’ making it big enough and sturdy enough to take the force of the weights without damaging the floor underneath.</p><p>So, if you choose to deadlift on platform, you end up protecting your floors.&nbsp;</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1700487236004" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1700487236004" data-row-gap="0px" data-extraclass=""><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1686320640542" data-id="1686320640542"><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1700487235962" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1700487235962" data-layout-lg="6+6" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="6+6" data-layout-sm="6+6" data-layout-xs="8+4" data-row-gap="0px"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-xs-8" id="c-1686566620521" data-id="1686566620521"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1700487235924" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1700487235924"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><b>Tips From the Champ</b></h2></div></div></div><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-xs-4" id="c-1686566621695" data-id="1686566621695"><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1700487236008" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1700487236008" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-right-lg gf-elm-right-md gf-elm-right-sm gf-elm-right-xs" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/d583efb1-a2f6-4d53-8a26-d6ddafaa60fd/7350738.png" alt="" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="512" height="512" data-width="50%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="512" natural-height="512"></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1700487235933" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1700487235933"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="">Another benefit of a deadlift platform you might not have considered is to do with a squat rack. If you want to fill out your home gym, a power rack or squat rack is pretty essential. But in order to stabilize the rack, you often have to bolt the equipment down into your floor. Homeowners might not want to do that, especially if they plan on moving the rack around at a later day. So, bolting it down on a deadlift platform is a good alternative.&nbsp;</div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1700487235989" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1700487235989" data-layout-lg="6+6" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="6+6" data-layout-sm="6+6" data-layout-xs="12+12" data-row-gap="0px"><div class="gf_column gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1686564763470" data-id="1686564763470"><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1700487236038" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1700487236038" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-exc=""><a href="https://torokhtiy.com/pages/oleksiy-torokhtiy" target="_blank"><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/fc0a1a19-2e31-4fa8-a43b-9c408a123923/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/Oleksiy.jpg" alt="" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="531" height="533" data-width="20%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="531" natural-height="533"></a></div></div></div><div class="gf_column gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1686564765807" data-id="1686564765807"><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1700487235939" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1700487235939"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><b><a href="https://torokhtiy.com/pages/oleksiy-torokhtiy" class="" target="_blank">Oleksiy Torokhtiy</a></b></p></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1700487236017" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1700487236017"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><span style="font-weight: 700;">Olympic Weightlifting&nbsp;</span><span style="font-weight: 700; color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">Champion</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1663068617801" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1663068617801"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Cut Down On The Noise</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1663068617800" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1663068617800"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Noise can be a big issue with weightlifting. Especially with Olympic style lifting as you’re dropping the weight repeatedly. Bumper plates can help reduce the noise, but not as well as a deadlift platform, which can almost deaden the thump of the weight as you drop it down. You can even get additional tools put in place to lower the noise even more.&nbsp;</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1663784050309" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1663784050309"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Practicing For Game Day</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1663784061070" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1663784061070"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>If you’re serious about your lifting and want to compete in powerlifting and Olympic weightlifting, then it’s always best to practice at home the same way you’ll be competing on game day. This means getting used to the surface area where you’ll be lifting in competition. So, having a home deadlift platform can be very valuable.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1663785185660" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1663785185660" data-resolution="3000x3000" style="display: block;"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/bd34f234-6f83-4694-af31-a5564b9e9d3d/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/athlet-with-barbell-on-deadlift-platform.jpg" alt="Athlet wogt Barbell on a Deadlift Platform" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1664025574435" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1664025574435"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">What To Look For In Deadlift Platform</h2></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1664025590632" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1664025590632"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Material</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1664025606594" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1664025606594"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>A deadlift platform can be made up of different materials. A common type is 11-gauge steel, as it’s both durable and will protect your floors. But you can also make your deadlift platform with a combination of rubber mats and wood, which can work equally well as long as it’s built correctly.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1664025615857" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1664025615857"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Size</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1664025625326" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1664025625326"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Similar to the materials, there are also a few different size options to choose from. A range of dimensions can go from 8 x 4 inches, which is a small deadlift platform. To an average of 8 x 6 inches, and a larger 8 x 8 inch platform. If you’re looking to just deadlift, then a 4 inch depth is suitable. If you want to do some Olympic weight lifting, then 6 or 8 inch depth comes into play.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1664025640892" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1664025640892"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Space Friendly</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1664025659598" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1664025659598"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>If you’re looking to build one at home, then you definitely need to be aware of the real estate it will take. Once the deadlift platform is set, it’ll be difficult to move it around, so measure correctly and pick out a space that you’ll be comfortable giving up for a while to your deadlifts.&nbsp;</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1663068617823" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1663068617823"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">FAQs</h2></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1663068617825" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1663068617825"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">How Big Does A Deadlift Platform Need To Be?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1663068617826" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1663068617826"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">A normal deadlift platform is <a href="https://www.catalystathletics.com/article/1895/How-to-Build-a-Weightlifting-Platform/" class="" target="_blank">8 feet wide and 4 feet tall</a>. Some platforms are even as long as 6 feet. This way, your floors stay protected, but you have enough space on the platform to do your exercise and also add and remove weight as you see fit.&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1663068617827" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1663068617827"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Which Wood Is Best For A Deadlift Platform?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1663068617828" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1663068617828"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">For a more secure and stable route, you want to use <a href="https://homeguides.sfgate.com/bc-plywood-99037.html" class="" target="_blank">BC grade plywood</a>. You can also use AB grade oak, depending on the price tag the wood comes with. But as long as the wood is B grade or better, you should be good to go.&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1664025757800" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1664025757800"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">How Thick Should Olympic Weightlifting Platforms Be?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1663068617830" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1663068617830"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">A typical weightlifting platform comes with 3/4" on the side. This is often plenty to absorb the impact of the weight. Especially if the sides of the platform are made of rubber. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size